---

import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Academics & Curriculum | Saraswati Shiksha Niketan Inter College"
	description="Explore the academic structure, curriculum, teaching methodology, and examination system at Saraswati Shiksha Niketan Inter College, Ghaziabad — Nursery to Class 12."
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	
>
 <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / <span>Academics</span></div>
      <h1>Academics</h1>
      <p>A structured, UP Board-aligned curriculum built to grow with your child, from their first alphabet to their board exams.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head center">
        <span class="eyebrow">Four Stages, One Continuous Journey</span>
        <h2>Our Academic Structure</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-4">
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="13.5" cy="6.5" r=".5"/><circle cx="17.5" cy="10.5" r=".5"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="7.5" r=".5"/><circle cx="6.5" cy="12.5" r=".5"/><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 0 0 0 20 2 2 0 0 0 0-4 2 2 0 0 1 0-4h4a2 2 0 0 0 2-2c0-5.5-4.5-10-10-10Z"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Nursery &amp; Primary</h3>
          <p class="person-role">Nursery – Class 5</p>
          <p>Play-based learning, phonics, numeracy foundations, and activity-driven classrooms that build a love for school.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polygon points="16.24 7.76 14.12 14.12 7.76 16.24 9.88 9.88 16.24 7.76"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Middle School</h3>
          <p class="person-role">Class 6 – 8</p>
          <p>Subject specialisation begins, with a focus on conceptual clarity, project work, and independent study habits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Secondary</h3>
          <p class="person-role">Class 9 – 10</p>
          <p>Board-focused preparation with structured revision, regular testing, and career-awareness sessions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 10 12 5 2 10l10 5 10-5Z"/><path d="M6 12v5c0 1.5 3 3 6 3s6-1.5 6-3v-5"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Senior Secondary</h3>
          <p class="person-role">Class 11 – 12</p>
          <p>Science, Commerce, and Humanities streams with focused subject teaching and entrance-exam guidance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="reveal image-frame"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509062522246-3755977927d7?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80" alt="Teacher explaining a concept to secondary school students" loading="lazy" class=""></div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">What We Teach &amp; How</span>
        <h2>Curriculum Overview</h2>
        <p class="lede">Our curriculum follows the Uttar Pradesh Board framework, enriched with supplementary resources in English communication, computer literacy, and general knowledge from an early age.</p>
        <ul class="check-list mt-lg">
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Core subjects: Hindi, English, Mathematics, Science, Social Science</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Science stream: Physics, Chemistry, Biology / Mathematics</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Commerce stream: Accountancy, Business Studies, Economics</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Humanities stream: History, Political Science, Geography, Economics</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Computer Science and IT introduced from Class 3 onward</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head center">
        <span class="eyebrow">How We Teach</span>
        <h2>Teaching Methodology</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card reveal"><div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 2v6.34a2 2 0 0 1-.24.96L3.6 18.4A2 2 0 0 0 5.36 21.5h13.28a2 2 0 0 0 1.76-3.1l-5.16-9.1a2 2 0 0 1-.24-.96V2"/><path d="M6.5 2h11"/><path d="M6.5 12.5h11"/></svg></div><h3>Activity-Based Learning</h3><p>Concepts introduced through experiments, models, and group activities rather than rote memorisation.</p></div>
        <div class="card reveal"><div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M8 21h8"/><path d="M12 17v4"/></svg></div><h3>Smart Classroom Teaching</h3><p>Digital content, videos, and interactive boards supplement traditional teaching for better retention.</p></div>
        <div class="card reveal"><div class="icon-badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14.5 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V7.5z"/><path d="M14 2v6h6"/><path d="M9 13h6"/><path d="M9 17h6"/></svg></div><h3>Continuous Assessment</h3><p>Regular class tests, monthly assessments, and structured feedback keep learning on track all year.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">Fair &amp; Transparent</span>
        <h2>Examination System</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card reveal">
          <h3>Internal Assessment</h3>
          <p>Unit tests, monthly tests, half-yearly, and pre-board examinations conducted through the academic year to track continuous progress and identify areas needing support.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <h3>Board Examinations</h3>
          <p>Class 10 and Class 12 students appear for UP Board examinations, supported by structured revision schedules, mock tests, and doubt-clearing sessions in the months leading up to exams.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head center">
        <span class="eyebrow">Plan Ahead</span>
        <h2>Academic Calendar Highlights — 2026-27</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-4">
        <div class="event-card reveal"><div class="event-date"><div class="d">01</div><div class="m">Apr</div></div><div><h4>Session Begins</h4><p>New academic year commences for all classes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="event-card reveal"><div class="event-date"><div class="d">20</div><div class="m">Sep</div></div><div><h4>Half-Yearly Exams</h4><p>Mid-session assessments across all classes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="event-card reveal"><div class="event-date"><div class="d">10</div><div class="m">Dec</div></div><div><h4>Pre-Board Exams Begin</h4><p>Class 10 &amp; 12 preparation intensifies.</p></div></div>
        <div class="event-card reveal"><div class="event-date"><div class="d">15</div><div class="m">Mar</div></div><div><h4>Annual Exams &amp; Results</h4><p>Final assessments and promotion to next class.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container split reverse-mobile">
      <div class="reveal image-frame"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1497633762265-9d179a990aa6?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80" alt="Students studying in the school library" loading="lazy" class=""></div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Support Beyond the Classroom</span>
        <h2>Learning Resources</h2>
        <p class="lede">Every student has access to resources designed to reinforce classroom learning and build independent study skills.</p>
        <ul class="check-list mt-lg">
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Fully stocked library with over 12,000 titles and reference material</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Subject-wise doubt-clearing sessions after school hours</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Digital learning content on smart classroom screens</li>
          <li><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg> Remedial classes for students needing extra academic support</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
